rratives and presses on.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aPOETRY / Canadian.2bisacsh  aTrauma Memoir.  aanti- narratives.  aauthorial self.  aautopathography.  abooks about amnesia.  acollective selves.  acritical disability studies.  adisability aesthetics.  aexperimental poetry.  afound poetry.  ahealing narrative.  alife writing.  alife-writing.  amedical narrative.  ameta commentary.  anarrative healing.  aneuro-trauma.  aneurotrauma.  aperson-centred narrative.  apost modern.  apost structuralism.  apost traumatic stress.  apost-modern.  apost-structuralism.  apost-traumatic writing.  apostmodern trauma.  apostmodern.  aposttrauma.  apsychodynamic narrative.  arecombinant found text.  aself-narration.  aself-reflexive.  atrauma and healing.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311127268908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2019z978311127498040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781773851136?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781773851136423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781773851136/original  a978-3-11-127268-9  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-127498-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles